<heading id="3E1D4846FFE5FFDAFF71F9F9FDE3F9E8" bold="true" box="[151,542,1579,1606]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" reason="4">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE5FFDAFF71F9F9FDE3F9E8" authority="(Cramer, 1777)" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[151,542,1579,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="procus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE5FFDAFF71F9F9FDE3F9E8" bold="true" box="[151,542,1579,1606]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE5FFDAFF71F9F9FE9FF9E8" bold="true" box="[151,354,1579,1606]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Eudocima procus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFE5FFDAFE97F9FEFDEBF9E8" author="Cramer, P." box="[369,534,1580,1606]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="97 - 192" refId="ref36795" refString="Cramer, P. (1777) De uitlandsche kapellen voorkomende in drie waereld-deelen Asia, Africa, en America by een verzameld en beschreeven 2. S. J. Baalde &amp; Barthelmemy Wild, Amesterdam &amp; Utrecht, 152 pp., pls. 97 - 192." type="book chapter" year="1777">Cramer, 1777</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFE5FFDAFF71F982FD78F824" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE5FFDAFF71F982FD85F9C5" blockId="13.[151,1437,1579,1931]" box="[151,632,1616,1643]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFE5FFDAFF79F982FF14F9C4" box="[159,233,1616,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[224,1364,194,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-19@59.[214,1373,181,1952]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 6. Neotropical Eudocima, Tetrisia, and Graphigona adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605510/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Figs 6</figureCitation>
: A–B, 18: A, 23: A–D, 30: B, 91: I)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE5FFDAFF71F9A6FD78F824" blockId="13.[151,1437,1579,1931]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
This species has a unique hindwing character: the medial patch is expanded into a median band extending across the entire wing from the costa to the inner margin. The band is comprised of four comma-shaped patches fused together. Other 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE5FFDAFF39F96EFE57F978" box="[223,426,1724,1750]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE5FFDAFF39F96EFEACF978" box="[223,337,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Eudocima</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
have at most two comma-shaped patches fused together. The hindwing marginal band is disjunct from the wing margin except between veins Cu2 and M3. Females without hindwings exposed could be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE5FFDAFEDDF8D7FE27F8B0" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[315,474,1796,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentifera">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE5FFDAFEDDF8D7FE27F8B0" box="[315,474,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E serpentifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE5FFDAFE19F8D7FD81F8B0" box="[511,636,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE5FFDAFE19F8D7FD85F8B0" baseAuthorityName="Schaus" baseAuthorityYear="1911" box="[511,632,1796,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colubra">E. colubra</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE5FFDAFD4BF8D7FCEAF8B0" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[685,791,1797,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="procus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE5FFDAFD4BF8D7FCEAF8B0" box="[685,791,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">E. procus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a contrasting pale triangle on the proximal side of the PM line between veins Cu2 and Cu1, which is absent in the other two species. This species feeds on 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE5FFDAFAEEF8FAFF01F8C8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Menispermaceae" genus="Odontocarya" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tamoides">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE5FFDAFAEEF8FAFF01F8C8" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Odontocarya tamoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE5FFDAFEECF89EFE31F8C9" baseAuthorityName="Zaspel" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[266,460,1868,1895]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Menispermaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Menispermaceae</taxonomicName>
) in 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE5FFDAFE10F89EFD9EF8C8" box="[502,611,1868,1894]" name="Honduras" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Honduras</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFE5FFDAFD97F89EFC9DF8C8" author="Caballero, R. &amp; Habeck, D. &amp; Andrews, K." box="[625,864,1868,1895]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="225 - 237" refId="ref36536" refString="Caballero, R., Habeck, D. &amp; Andrews, K. (1994) Clave ilustrada para larvas de noctuidos de importancia economica de El Salvador, Honduras y Nicaragua. CEIBA, 35 (2), 225 - 237." type="journal article" year="1994">
Caballero 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE5FFDAFD00F89FFCEBF8C8" box="[742,790,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">et al</emphasis>
. 1994
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE5FFDAFC94F89EFBC8F8C8" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[882,1077,1868,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="procus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE5FFDAFC94F89EFBC8F8C8" box="[882,1077,1868,1894]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Eudocima procus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is relatively common and widespread from 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE5FFDAFEC3F8A2FE8AF824" box="[293,375,1904,1930]" name="Bolivia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE5FFDAFE48F8A3FE1CF825" box="[430,481,1905,1931]" name="Peru" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Peru</collectingCountry>
up to 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE5FFDAFDCEF8A2FD7CF824" box="[552,641,1904,1930]" name="Mexico" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Mexico</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
